STACK MANIPULATION

push pop
stack moves towards lower address - descending stack

push {r1,r2} -> first r1 will be pushed, then r2 will be pushed into stack
stack address will decrement by 8 bytes(4+4) after 2 values are pushed into it

pop {r2,r1} -> stack value will pop to r2, then pop to r1 and stack address will increment
sp will always point to current free address

SRAM start address 0x20000000 - stm32vl
SRAM size - 32 KB
stack size is 4kb so stack pointer should be 0x20001000(first entry of vector table) =  0x20000000 + 4kb

push operation - first decrements address then pushes vales
