how cpu runs multiple tasks?

all tasks are while(1) loop - 
tasks can be switched among by scheduler by manipulating pc
info should be saved whenever task is switched - save pc, and some GPRs

anatomy of task
- each task has its own stack
- cpu registers are stored into stack then task is switched
- cpu registers include pc(r14)
- with each systick interrupt, sp is updated, so that context can be switched when task extracts stack, consequently loading new pc value 
- systick interrupt whenever it comes global registers are saved, local registers need to be saved, change the sp to new value, when cpu goes back to handler mode, cpu starts from new stack, popping global registers automatically, local registers should be popped manually, hence loading new pc value
- systick isr is the scheduler

