- configuration of systick handler to be within reset handler
- load systick_csr to r0
- load systick_rvr to r1
- load systick_cvr to r2
- load timeout to r3, timeout is 24 bit timer value currently set to 0x000fffff

- store the value in r3 to address at r1
str r3, [r1] - timeout to be stored in rvr - rvr hold the reload value, so timer starts decrementing from 0x000fffff till 0
- clear r3
mov r3,#0x00
- store the value in r3 to address at r2, current value of timer is cleared to 0
str r3, [r2]
- set last 3 bits of r3 to 1 
mov r3, #0x7
- store the value in r3 to address at r0, control status register, bit 0,1,2 set to 1
str r3, [r0]

- initialise register r5 with value 0, since r5 is not part of stack frame, it wont be restored when exception returns

- within systick handler, increment the value of r5
- at the end of exception handler place bx lr, so that cpu can exit isr, here lr stores special value to indicate cpu it has returned from isr

