- playing with push/pop to save context in systick
-----------------------------------------
- push r4 to r7 on stack
push {r4-r7}
- move (r8 to r11) on (r0 to r3)
- push r0 to r3 on stack
- push operation is divided in two parts, because push instruction can only fetch registers r0 to r7, because 3 bits are used up in encoding registers
- registers r4 to r11 are not part of stack frame so they need to be pushed manually on stack
- restoring context happens through pop command, by following exact opposite sequence of above
pop {r0,r3} -> moves stack data to (r0,r3)
move (r0,r3) on (r8,r11)
pop {r4,r7} -> moves stack data to (r4,r7)
- however before restoring context sp should be changed, so that r4-r11 are restored from new stack
- stack for each task is stored in ram, and pc value in each stack should be that particular function name
